        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I know everyone would like to see all sorts of changes but I think there is one serious issue left to fix when it comes to pets and raiding.  The resists are as good as ours so we can't improve on that.  It's too bad that pet hold is a class skill but... what're ya gunna do?  It's required when you fight AE mobs so you don't get early aggro but at least it'll be available to those 59+ that work for it.  It's easy for our healers to heal our pets now with the new UI because they can see our pet's health just as easily as they can see my health.  Hell, I can even see what buffs or debuffs/DoTs are on my pet so I can either rebuff him or get him cured.  There is still a problem though.  I have to ask for single buffs.  I really don't want to do that.  Every pet getting single buffs increases the mana/regent usage a lot.  Pets need to get hit with group buffs/heals.  They, currently, are not even hit with AE bard songs or mass group buffs as I learned from the new /pet report health output.  That puts them at a serious disadvantage and just serves to sponge up more of the healer's mana.</P><P>A lot of the other posts for requested pet changes would be nice... but that's all they would be.  Nice.  This is almost required to effectivly use pets on raids.  What would be REALLY nice is if AEs on me/the pet diddn't cause pet aggro.  When you're pulling 3-4 mobs that all AE, it's IMPOSSIBLE to use a pet and I don't feel that the minumum of a level 59 with 21 aa points is a reasonable requirement to use a pet in an AE situation.  That's half of what these pet changes are about, right?  So we can use them on raids and not get them destroyed by AEs.  That's a change I can live without.  I mean, there IS an avenue to correct that problem eventualy.</P><P>Once my pet can get buffed without me bugging everyone for single buffs, I feel pets are fixed as much as they can be for raids and the rest is just eye candy or coolness factor.</P><P>Oh, and pets suffer in ae dispel situations as they don't have insta click buffs at their disposal... but that is just one of the disadvantages of being a pet, I guess.</P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock</font></td>

