        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         First, if you think that the max pet level adjustment was for us - you are kidding yourselves.  Pet resistances?  Same thing.  Shamans and, to some degree, mages were meant to benefit from it.  We were a by-product, nothing more.  The necro changes of late have been downright insulting to my intelligence.  Even the propsed DoT stacking is so Shamans can DoT more effectively.  When was the last time so many necros showed up to one of your raids and had problems working out who was casting which DoT(s)?  Never seen it.</P><P>To Do List for VI to balance Necros:</P><P>1.  Fix the pet models - use already existing models to 'save space' (ala the monster summon line for mages) and make the class happy from a look perspective.  Change the lich form to be different from our pets, too.</P><P>2.  Make rare sub-50 spells more common, and 50+ spells more in-line with other classes for rarity.  Don't give 'em to us, but at least make it reasonable compared to other classes.</P><P>3.  Make Group taps last longer.  2 Mins on a 300+ mana spell is just too darn short.  And make lesser versions available to lower level necros.</P><P>4.  Lich line spells should make you non-kos to undead.  It may sound too powerful, but it just makes too much sense.  Compare to Enchanter illusion spells, and it makes a helluva lot of sense.</P><P>5.  Fix EE spells - either reduce the recast time on Infusion, or make the regent a peridot.</P><P>6.  Make Lifetaps Lure spells.  Lure only mobs keep us on the side lines, and noone should be on the sidelines during big battles.</P><P>7.  Take the Mass Group Buff AA ability away and replace it with something that actually makes sense for necros.  We get one group buff spell, what the heck would we want this AA ability for?</P><P>8.  Give us Death Peace - Seems silly that SK's get a better Necromancy spell then a NECROMANCER.</P><P>9.  Make undead mobs classify as UNDEAD.  I am very tired of clicking my spell gem with a skeleton targetted and seeing "This Spell Only Works on Undead".</P><P>10. Make our debuff spells line (Scent line) include magic resist and make it stackable with Tash line spells.  This alone would increase our raid value.</P><P>I am sure I missed something...but this list would quell alot of my concerns with what I still think is the coolest class in the game.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
