        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I would like to sse something discussed with Verant (argh...is it possible btw to discuss with them ?) : pet aggro.</P><P>This is my opinion, would like too to know what you think about that. First, this is not a Necro only concern but mainly Mage / Necro one, then any other pet class. Main thing about pets for those 2 classes (and mainly Mages) is that pet is one of their weapon, surely the best Mages get, a very good one for us. BUT pets are the main source of danger because of pathing and aggro. Imagine making pets non aggro, I mean something like pet able to run by mobs and being absolutely indiff to them. This would fix this problem...as long as pet isn't engaged in combat, pet is indiff. Why then would a mage or a Nec being forbidden from making a pet ? This is an important issue if you ask me, do you know any Warrior removing his primary and / or secondary weapon just because this weapon will cause a train due to pathing, which can be seen as a bug ? I don't know any...but I know many Mages / Necros refusing to summon a pet just because it would make them die (something here to help them that makes them die, am I the only one that found this a bit silly ???).</P><P>Then, if pet isn't aggro at all, why don't let summoner the ability to become invis and thus, moving thru mobs without any risk (like EVERYBODY else with their weapons !). Just make pet unable to attack any mob while summoner is invis and exploit would be avoided, is it that difficult ? Just do the same thing that pet unable to attack mezzed mobs and that is. Why forcing Necros / Mages to kill their pets just to move from a spot to another ?</P><P>Point is : Pet Summoners are quite fairly balanced WITH their pets, absolutely not without BUT Pet Summoners MUST chose either to use their main weapon and a real risk to die OR not use them and then, being useless...our choice in really too many situations is being useless or die...is that fair ? When you know the cost of some pets (EoT is the highest toll to pay, keeping also 2 inventory slots used for them...still fair).</P><P>To avoid a little further exploits, a pet summoner that launches his pet to attack and then trying to become invis should make pet stopping attack (but still being hit by mobs) and can't defend himself while summoner is invis...or making summoner much more aggro...dunno but something that would prevent summoner to become invis.</P><P>But please, don't let our best weapon being our favorite danger any longer.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
